    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-10-05T01:25:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-10-05T01:25:00-05:00" n="672"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d672">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/1602: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Addis Ababa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-05T09:00:00+02:35"
                            >October 5, 1935—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 5:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>111. Your 63, October 3, 6 p.m.<note n="9" xml:id="d672fn9">See footnote 6a, <ref
                            target="#pg_790">p. 790</ref>.</note> Technically no state of war exists
                    as yet. Ethiopian Government has not handed the Italian Minister his passport
                    nor has the latter asked for them.</p>
                <p>The Department may depend on my watching developments closely.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
